title: For Sale:  Vintage Mossberg Rifle - 151M(a)
postcontent: This is a Mossberg Model 151M(a) semi-auto rifle.  It's chambered in 22 lr and has a 15 round tubular magazine that is loaded in the butt stock. The barrel is 20" and it weighs around 7 lbs. The stock is a two-piece Mannlicher style stock with pistol grip, cheekpiece and swivels.  Most you see are missing the swivels and they go for up to $100 on eBay.  The front sight is the No. 1A ramp front sight that has a removable hood and 4 different style blades that flip-up.  The rear peep sight is a No. S130 receiver sight. This rifle was made between 1946 - 1947.I could split up the sights and swivels on this rifle and make about as much as I'm asking, but it would be a shame to do that to such a nice piece of history.  They simply do not make 22 rifles like this anymore.

postcontent: This is the uncommon steel-framed (instead of aluminum) Stoeger Luger in .22lr with a 4.5" barrel and checkered grips. This particular version was made in the 80s. It is patterned off the P08 and is legally a Luger, since Stoeger took ownership of the name. It is a fun shooter that mimics a 9mm Luger and its famous toggle action. I tried Remington Golden Bullets and it had many failure-to-fires. It also had a failure to extract. I spend most of my time in SLO and can meet in the nearby towns.
